         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">8/7/78. ¶  ¶ I merely write a few lines, dear Prof De Caisne, to say, that I have forwarded to the Institute by this post a copy of the English Edition (enlarged by me) of Wittsteins Chemistry of plan...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">78.07.08</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Decaisne</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Bibliothèque de l'Institut de France, Paris.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">8/7/78.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I merely write a few lines, dear Prof De Caisne, to say, that I have forwarded to the Institute by this post a copy of the English Edition (enlarged by me) of Wittsteins Chemistry of plants.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Wittstein (1878), i.e. B78.06.09.</p>
               </note> I can send to M. Chevreul, Baron Dumas, yourself &amp; other savants a copy of this translation, if desired. I hope you receive the fragmenta &amp;c regularly.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>As I have occasion to write to you, I would like to remark, that I have for several years past received <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">not the slightest acknowledgement</hi>
               </seg> in the publications of france for <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">my enormous</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">efforts</hi>
               </seg> since nearly a quarter of a Century to push Eucalyptus culture into the mediterranean regions. For a long time, except by Mons le Doct. Planchon in the revue de deux mondes,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">Planchon (1875a).</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> and by Dr Raveret-Wattel in his meritorious work on Eucalyptus,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Raveret-Wattel (1875).</p>
               </note> my name did not even appear on any occasion, altho' I had not only <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">much toil</hi>
               </seg> but also <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">much expense</hi>
               </seg> to promote and almost <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">originate</hi>
               </seg> this culture of E Globulus in the mediterranean countries.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Has recently anything appeared on New Caledonian plants in the Annales des sciences naturelles? If so, please send me kindly the respective numbers, so that I may not overlook anything, when working on Papuan Plants. I never received any number of the Annales, since the large sending by M. Adolphe Brogniart<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">i.e. A. Brongniart.</p>
               </note> &amp; yourself several years ago.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Does Dr Bureau allow me to work up some of the New Caledonian orders? I would undertake <name key="Rubiaceae">Rubiaceae</name>, <name key="Leguminosae">Leguminosae</name> &amp; <name key="Myrtaceae">Myrtaceae</name>, Dr Beccari intending also to give over to me these orders of his large collections.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">What do you think of my "select plants"?<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B76.12.04.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
